# hooks
- label: --json create, --json set, --json unset, --json rm, --json link, and --json unlink mutations whose matching Hook fails or times out after the Store mutation commits exit non-zero, leave stdout empty, report the committed Hook failure or timeout on stderr, and persist both the Store mutation and Hook Run
  id: jhf
  command: cargo test --quiet --test hook_stress json_mutation_hook_failure_or_timeout_reports_committed_without_success_json -- --list --ignored | grep -qx "json_mutation_hook_failure_or_timeout_reports_committed_without_success_json: test" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && agent-store hook add create k=v -- "exit 1" >/dev/null && ! agent-store --json create note k=v >out 2>err && test ! -s out && grep -q "already committed" err && test "$(agent-store find --count)" = 1 && test "$(agent-store hook runs --json | jq ".hook_runs | length")" = 1
  tags: [implemented]
- label: --json create, --json set, --json unset, --json rm, --json link, and --json unlink mutations with multiple matching Hooks run matching Hooks sequentially in registration order (oldest Hook first, not Hook-ID order) after commit; when one or more earlier-registered Hooks succeed and a later-registered Hook fails or times out, the mutation remains committed, the successful and failing or timed-out Hook Runs persist, later-registered matching Hooks do not run, stdout stays empty, and stderr reports the committed Hook failure or timeout
  id: 9ev
  command: cargo test --quiet --test hook_stress json_multiple_matching_hooks_stop_after_failure_or_timeout -- --list --ignored | grep -qx "json_multiple_matching_hooks_stop_after_failure_or_timeout: test" && d=$(mktemp -d) && cd $d && agent-store init >/dev/null && agent-store hook add create k=v -- "touch first-ran" >/dev/null && agent-store hook add create k=v -- "exit 1" >/dev/null && agent-store hook add create k=v -- "touch third-ran" >/dev/null && ! agent-store --json create note k=v >out 2>err && test ! -s out && test -f first-ran && test ! -f third-ran && grep -q "already committed" err && test "$(agent-store hook runs --json | jq ".hook_runs | length")" = 2
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Plain create, --json rm, plain link, --json unlink, plain single-field set, --json single-field unset, plain multi-field set, and --json multi-field unset mutations whose matching Hook fails after commit still invoke the failing Hook with stable AGENT_STORE_EVENT, AGENT_STORE_ID, and AGENT_STORE_KIND; representative multi-Hook plain single-field set and --json link failures give every successful Hook and the failing Hook the same stable base and applicable field or link env while skipping later-registered Hooks; create, rm, and multi-field record mutations omit misleading link or single-field env, link mutations include relation/target env, single-field record mutations include field key/value old/new env with spaces, equals signs, quotes, backslashes, and newlines preserved for hook consumers, stdout remains empty, JSON mode keeps stdout empty on Hook failure, and the Store mutation and Hook Runs persist
  id: 06p
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_failure_preserves_link_context_env
  tags: [implemented]
